2. Load data from SQL Server into Power BI Desktop


A. Loading Class_Management Data

Step 1. Open Power BI Desktop and on the upper left ribbon, click on get data and choose SQL Server.

Step 2.  For the log in credentials of the data source use server name and database name provided below:

              Server: hypv8669.hostedbyappliedi.net

              Database: CCPP

Select import mode then click on OK.

Step 3. Follow the rest of the steps shown on the GIF below.


Note, follow the instructions in the attached word document if you encounter the following error message.


B. Loading Curriculum Data into Power BI Desktop following steps shown on the GIF below.

Here is the query you will enter for sql statement.

SELECT                  *

FROM                   (

                                                                                select                    DISTINCT PathName, CourseName, CourseOrder, SectionName, SectionOrder

                                                                                from                      [dbo].[vw_Curriculum]

                                                                                where                   PathID = 1000

                                                                                AND                                       CourseID IN (1000,1001,1002) A




C. Create a dataset for distinct classes.

Query needed for this step:

SELECT DISTINCT [ClassName]

FROM [dbo].[vw_QS_MetricsDashboard_ClassManagement]

WHERE Class_SessionDate >= DATEADD(M, -3, GETDATE())

AND Class_ClassInstructor IS NOT NULL
